Pierce. Do you still have
the number of that private
investigator you used

14:53.392 --> 14:55.292
when you thought Ross Perot
was sleeping with your mom?

14:55.494 --> 14:57.758
Is this about that guy in your class?
Yeah.

14:57.963 --> 15:01.296
Face the facts.
This kid's got some natural talent
you just don't have.

15:01.500 --> 15:04.196
How would you know?
It's all over the school.

15:04.403 --> 15:05.836
Great.

15:07.373 --> 15:10.308
Why aren't you in sailing class?
They drowned me.

15:10.509 --> 15:12.204
Why?
For a better grade.

15:12.411 --> 15:15.175
But weren't we discussing
your flaws, Jeff?

15:15.381 --> 15:18.680
Why are you letting
this guy get to you?
What's really going on?

15:18.884 --> 15:20.283
I made a bad pot.

15:22.922 --> 15:26.858
For some reason,
I always thought that
I was special and different.

15:27.059 --> 15:30.256
And I guess I just have
a really hard time

15:30.462 --> 15:34.057
when I want to be good
at something and I suck.

15:34.566 --> 15:35.863
Uh-huh.

15:38.938 --> 15:40.405
Here, give me a hand.

15:40.606 --> 15:43.404
What are you doing?
I'm going back to my sailing class.

15:43.609 --> 15:44.940
After they murdered you?

15:45.144 --> 15:46.611
Jeffrey, when I was born,

15:46.812 --> 15:49.178
I got my umbilical cord
wrapped around my neck,

15:49.381 --> 15:50.939
both arms and one of my ankles.

15:51.150 --> 15:54.085
Mom said there came
a point when the doctors
stopped delivering me

15:54.286 --> 15:56.186
and just started laughing. Heh.

15:56.388 --> 16:00.188
I mean, if I ever let being bad
at something stop me,

16:00.392 --> 16:01.791
I wouldn't even be here.

16:02.494 --> 16:06.225
That thing some men call failure?
I call living.

16:06.432 --> 16:08.024
Breakfast.

16:08.233 --> 16:11.634
And I'm not leaving
till I've cleaned out the buffet.

16:11.837 --> 16:13.805
Now, how about a shove?

16:18.677 --> 16:20.645
[§§§]

16:21.413 --> 16:23.438
Good luck, Pierce.
Don't need it.

16:23.649 --> 16:25.446
Never had it.

16:28.921 --> 16:30.684
Britta,
trim the boom flat.

16:30.889 --> 16:32.823
Troy, sit windward
to heel the boat.

16:33.025 --> 16:35.960
My, the sea has a worthy opponent.

16:37.363 --> 16:39.888
Oh, my God, it's Pierce.

16:40.099 --> 16:42.067
[§§§]

16:44.703 --> 16:47.399
Man, that guy's life
is one big joke.

16:52.177 --> 16:53.474
I mean, I feel bad for him,

16:53.679 --> 16:56.307
but things have been running
smoother since he drowned.

16:56.515 --> 16:58.540
I bet he gets that
all the time.

